  "prompt": "What is luvox good for?",
  "response": "Luvox, which contains the active ingredient fluvoxamine, is primarily used to treat obsessive-compulsive disorder (OCD) and social anxiety disorder (social phobia). It belongs to a class of medications known as selective serotonin reuptake inhibitors (SSRIs), which work by increasing the levels of serotonin in the brain, thereby helping to improve mood, anxiety, and other symptoms associated with these conditions.\n\nAdditionally, Luvox may sometimes be prescribed for other conditions, such as depression and post-traumatic stress disorder (PTSD), though its use for these indications might be less common compared to its primary uses. As with all medications, it's important to use Luvox under the guidance of a healthcare professional, who can provide personalized advice and monitor for side effects.",
